CLAS Course Registration Resources

August, 2022

To review your current course schedule:

  • Go to my.mercer.edu.
  • Login your student account.
  • On the left sidebar, expand Academics, then click My Class Schedule. The page shows
    1. Summary of all the courses you are currently enrolled in.
    2. A calendar-style time sheet for all your classes. (Choose a week, e.g., Week 2 for a complete preview.)

Degree Overview

GenEd Checklist

This is Mercer University Foundational Studies (General Education) checklist for the academic year 2022-2023. It can be found on the web page https://liberalarts.mercer.edu/resources/student-resources/.

You are expected to enroll in one of the two General Education tracks (your preference):

  • INT: the Integrative program
  • GBK: the Great Book program.

Catalog

This is the Mercer University catalog for the academic year 2022-2023. The catalog can pretty much answer ALL your questions regarding academics at Mercer. The official copy is available on https://registrar.mercer.edu/macon/catalogs.cfm.

  • To find the requirements for a specific major/minor (e.g., Biology):
    • Click on the search button located on the top right corner of the document below.
    • Type in Biology (BIO) and press the Enter/Return key.
  • To look up the course description for a specific class (e.g., HIS 105):
    • Click on the search button located on the top right corner of the document below.
    • Type in HIS 105. and press the Enter/Return key.
    • Click the button until you land on the course description page.

(If you dont see a document below, you may need to refresh your browser a couple of times.)

Pre-Health Professions

Please visit Academic Advising Services (AAS) website.

  • Select your pre-health profession on AASs website to see the specific page for the your desired track..
  • Click on Scheduling of pre-XXXX Coursework to see suggested schedules.

Searching for Classes

This panel displays the real time class meeting schedule at Mercer University. Please be patient, it takes a while for this panel to show up and update. Bookmark the original link https://adminapps.mercer.edu/classroomsched/default.aspx?C=M for future reference.

To search for a class:

  • Select Term: 2022 Fall
  • Type in a course code. For example, MAT 191.
  • The third column is the section number. Be sure to read all rows with the same section number.
  • Dont forget to check the column # of Seats Available.
  • If there are multiple pages in the search result, navigate to other pages by clicking on the page numbers in the botton of the table.
